<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
    AccessibilityService configuration for CopyPaste clipboard monitoring.

    Android 10+ (API 29+) blocks background clipboard reads from regular apps.
    The two sanctioned exceptions are:
      1. Default Input Method Editor (IME) — not applicable here.
      2. Enabled AccessibilityService — used here.

    IMPORTANT LIMITS (Android 10+):
    Even with an AccessibilityService enabled, OnPrimaryClipChangedListener still
    fires to notify that the clipboard changed, but ClipboardManager.getPrimaryClip()
    returns null from a background context UNLESS the process calling it is the
    AccessibilityService process itself (which it is here — ClipboardAccessibilityService
    runs in the same process). This means the AccessibilityService route DOES work for
    capturing clipboard content, with two caveats:
      a) The user must manually enable the service in Settings > Accessibility.
      b) Some OEMs (e.g. MIUI) add extra restrictions on top of AOSP that may still
         block clipboard reads even from an enabled AccessibilityService. There is no
         workaround for those without root.

    Android 12+ toast: The system shows a one-time "App accessed your clipboard" toast
    the first time per-session that getPrimaryClip() is called. This is expected and
    cannot be suppressed.

    accessibilityEventTypes="typeWindowStateChanged" — a single minimal flag
      (AAPT rejects "0"/none); the service ignores the events anyway.
    feedbackType="feedbackGeneric" — minimal feedback declaration required by framework.
    canRetrieveWindowContent="false" — explicitly opt-out of screen reading.
    notificationTimeout="0" — not applicable since we subscribe to no events.

    The service exists SOLELY to hold the AccessibilityService binding so that
    ClipboardManager grants clipboard access to this process in the background.
    It does NOT observe, read, or report any screen content, key events, or
    accessibility events.
-->
<accessibility-service xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:accessibilityEventTypes="typeWindowStateChanged"
    android:accessibilityFeedbackType="feedbackGeneric"
    android:accessibilityFlags="flagDefault"
    android:canRetrieveWindowContent="false"
    android:description="@string/accessibility_service_description"
    android:notificationTimeout="0"
    android:settingsActivity=".OnboardingActivity" />
